  "prompt": "What is 6/6 myopia vision?",
  "response": "The term \"6/6 vision\" refers to visual acuity measurement in metric units, which is equivalent to \"20/20 vision\" in feet. This is considered normal vision, meaning that you can see at 6 meters what a person with normal vision can see at the same distance. \n\nMyopia, or nearsightedness, is a common refractive error where distant objects appear blurry while close objects can be seen clearly. A person with myopia will have a visual acuity measurement that indicates worse vision than 6/6, such as 6/12 or 6/18, depending on the severity of the condition. Therefore, \"6/6 myopia vision\" would be a contradictory term because having myopia means your vision is not 6/6 without correction.",
